DefaultFontManager
public interface FontManager<C extends ViewComponent>
extends ViewManager

The FontManager is a ViewManager which handles the font attribute for ViewComponents.

This interface describes methods for setting the default, maximal allowed, minimal allowed and actually font size as well as the font. The maximum and minimum font size for instance are important for the layout process.

The basic implementation of this interface is DefaultFontManager To extend or overwrite some of the basic functionalities the DefaultFontManager should be extended.

The extending of the ViewManager interface ensures the communication with the observed view.

Author:
Andreas Held
